summary: I made a Marvel themed eyeshadow palette. Took me a long time because I can’t Photoshop for the life of me. Each colour was...
caption:
I made a Marvel themed eyeshadow palette. Took me a long time because I can’t Photoshop for the life of me. Each colour was based directly from comics and only movies if the colour repeated itself (Spider-Man). I’m lowkey proud of myself but I’m terrible at art.

The beauty community needs to make more colourful products.

Yes, I know the text looks awful. I’m not completely happy with Strange’s and Thor’s colours. 

This was originally the Sweet Peach Palette from Too Faced.

Side note: I couldn’t do one eyeshadow for each movie because there’s too many superheroes. (No Guardians of the Galaxy)

summary: Everyone’s talking about how Tony’ll be in his 20’s during Captain Marvel
body:
Everyone’s talking about how Tony’ll be in his 20’s during Captain Marvel

But here I am thinking Tony and Carol might’ve known each other prior to her getting kidnapped by the Kree, and now she has no memories when it’s a very real possibility this movie takes place post december 16, 1996.

title: Itsy Bitsy Spider
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2DcHfpQ

by eccentric_artist_221b

Tony wants to give the boy a squeeze, but the webs hold his arms back, so he slumps backwards in surrender.

“No more churros before bed,” he murmurs, nuzzling his cheek against Peter’s forehead. “We are definitely adding that to the rules of the house.”
